00:14:22,061 --> 00:14:25,130
and Huwei seemed to be
able to understand that calmly.

244
00:14:25,197 --> 00:14:29,168
That acceptance he showed his mom,
that shows his real emotional maturity.

245
00:14:29,235 --> 00:14:33,205
And his mom was still able
to assure him that he's still her son.

246
00:14:33,272 --> 00:14:35,741
- That he'll never change, no matter what.
- True.

247
00:14:35,808 --> 00:14:37,109
It's really rare

248
00:14:37,843 --> 00:14:39,678
for a coming out story to be accepted

249
00:14:39,745 --> 00:14:43,015
in all the ways
you hoped for or you had imagined.

250
00:14:43,082 --> 00:14:44,550
In life,

251
00:14:44,617 --> 00:14:46,819
even if you're related by blood,

252
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,655
there are some things
you just can't relate to each other about.

253
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:51,123
- There are.
- Right?

254
00:14:51,690 --> 00:14:56,962
But there are times when I think you
don't have to be bound by those rules.

255
00:14:57,029 --> 00:15:02,701
With family, you want them to understand
and accept you twice as much.

256
00:15:02,768 --> 00:15:04,970
But I think it's completely okay

257
00:15:05,037 --> 00:15:10,476
to build your own kind of family
with friends or partners who cry with you.

258
00:15:10,542 --> 00:15:11,744
Truly.

259
00:15:12,678 --> 00:15:15,514
For someone like Huwei,
who rarely shows emotion,

260
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:18,217
<i>having someone</i>
<i>he can share his pain with,</i>

261
00:15:18,284 --> 00:15:22,087
and who he can say, "It hurts," to,
must be really reassuring.

262
00:15:22,154 --> 00:15:23,389
That's so true.

263
00:15:23,455 --> 00:15:26,025
I think it must have been
incredibly reassuring

264
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:27,760
to have someone who could cry with him,

265
00:15:27,826 --> 00:15:30,429
sharing this same pain
as if it were his own.

