"It became routine for us
to spend Christmas

330
00:19:00,973 --> 00:19:03,709
and New Year's together every year."

331
00:19:03,775 --> 00:19:05,978
<i>"Pre-ordering a Christmas cake together,</i>

332
00:19:06,044 --> 00:19:08,514
<i>and then going out to buy</i>
<i>Christmas chicken on Christmas Day,</i>

333
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:10,415
<i>fully expecting a long line."</i>

334
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:13,285
<i>"We'd talk about what to make</i>
<i>for Christmas dinner each year,</i>

335
00:19:13,352 --> 00:19:14,786
<i>whether to buy chicken or not."</i>

336
00:19:14,853 --> 00:19:16,355
<i>"One year, we made cream stew."</i>

337
00:19:16,421 --> 00:19:18,857
- <i>He remembers every tiny detail.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

338
00:19:19,358 --> 00:19:23,328
"<i>We decided to take the dogs</i>
<i>on a little trip to Awaji Island."</i>

339
00:19:24,196 --> 00:19:26,865
<i>"Every time the dogs went</i>
<i>to peek at his face,</i>

340
00:19:26,932 --> 00:19:29,801
<i>he'd pet their heads</i>
<i>and talk to them gently."</i>

341
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:33,305
<i>"I fell asleep watching him do that."</i>

342
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:37,809
<i>"He told me he was thinking</i>
<i>about buying a house."</i>

343
00:19:38,544 --> 00:19:41,013
<i>"Come to think of it,</i>
<i>I think the realtor asked us,</i>

344
00:19:41,079 --> 00:19:42,447
<i>'What's your relationship?'"</i>

345
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:46,251
<i>"At the time, I smiled and answered,</i>
<i>'We're like family.'"</i>

346
00:19:47,252 --> 00:19:51,290
<i>"That might've been the first time</i>
<i>I used the word 'family' to describe us."</i>

347
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:57,396
And I think…

348
00:19:57,896 --> 00:20:00,365
This is the last page. This is a bit…

349
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:07,706
Um… "Around the time
the Labrador retriever turned 14…

350
00:20:08,273 --> 00:20:10,375
he started eating less and less."

351
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:12,444
"When he couldn't eat anymore,

352
00:20:12,511 --> 00:20:15,514
the thought that it was almost time
crossed my mind."

353
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:22,087
"He also said quietly,
'He might only have a few more days.'"

354
00:20:24,156 --> 00:20:26,625
"A few days after he stopped eating,

355
00:20:27,259 --> 00:20:30,495
he said,
'I'm going to sleep with Jazz tonight.'"

356
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:33,298
"When I woke up in the morning,
he was already awake,

357
00:20:33,365 --> 00:20:36,501
and it seemed like he had
been watching over him all night."

358
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:39,938
"At around 10:00 a.m. that day,

359
00:20:40,505 --> 00:20:45,544
I heard, 'Jazz! Jazz!'
coming from the second floor."

360
00:20:46,144 --> 00:20:48,247
"When I hurried up to the second floor,

361
00:20:51,783 --> 00:20:54,720
he said to me through tears,
'He just stopped breathing.'"

362
00:21:00,158 --> 00:21:03,695
"He cried for a while
as he stroked Jazz's body."

363
00:21:05,631 --> 00:21:07,065
"I cried just like him,

364
00:21:07,132 --> 00:21:10,469
but when I thought about how much more
time he had spent with Jazz,

365
00:21:10,535 --> 00:21:12,704
and how it must've
hurt more for him,

366
00:21:12,771 --> 00:21:15,474
I couldn't say anything to him
at the time."

367
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:20,545
"It was the first time
I had ever seen him cry so hard."

368
00:21:23,548 --> 00:21:26,184
When it comes to relationships,

369
00:21:26,251 --> 00:21:31,356
my top non-negotiable is that
my partner must love animals.

370
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:33,759
And in that regard,

371
00:21:34,793 --> 00:21:40,132
I think he loves animals more than
anyone else I've ever met.

372
00:21:40,198 --> 00:21:41,967
Yeah, more than anyone else.

373
00:21:42,034 --> 00:21:44,703
Mmm. He really was…

374
00:21:46,705 --> 00:21:49,408
He really is a very loving person.

375
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:50,509
Mmm.

376
00:21:55,714 --> 00:21:58,417
- Wanna do a random clothes swap?
- Sure, let's do that.

377
00:21:58,483 --> 00:22:01,787
And in the morning,
we'll sit down and be like, "Huh?"

378
00:22:02,287 --> 00:22:05,557
"We've switched places!"

379
00:22:05,624 --> 00:22:07,826
<i>Tomoaki? Tomoaki?</i>

380
00:22:07,893 --> 00:22:10,062
- All together. "Huh?"
- <i>I'm so happy.</i>

381
00:22:10,128 --> 00:22:11,763
"We've switched places!"

382
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:15,067
Tomorrow morning,
we'll wear whatever's hanging in your room

383
00:22:15,133 --> 00:22:16,201
and come here.

384
00:22:16,268 --> 00:22:17,235
Got it.

385
00:22:18,904 --> 00:22:23,275
<i>Hey! Make way for some madness</i>

386
00:22:25,043 --> 00:22:26,278
<i>Move over</i>

387
00:22:29,748 --> 00:22:31,316
- Here.
- <i>Did they swap?</i>

388
00:22:31,383 --> 00:22:33,685
<i>Everyone's wearing each other's clothes.</i>

389
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:38,123
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

390
00:22:38,557 --> 00:22:40,559
- Wait…
- Everyone looks different.

391
00:22:40,625 --> 00:22:42,627
- You change your look?
- Different!

392
00:22:43,128 --> 00:22:48,100
The fashion witch Tomoaki went ahead
and changed the clothes.

393
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:49,801
<i>Fashion witch Tomoaki?</i>

394
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:51,503
- This is fun.
- Thank you!

395
00:22:51,570 --> 00:22:52,471
<i>Looks fun.</i>

396
00:22:52,537 --> 00:22:54,539
- Thank you, witch.
- Witch.

397
00:22:55,273 --> 00:22:56,975
- Rally good.
- This was fun.

398
00:22:57,075 --> 00:23:00,011
- Aki the Witch.
- Every once in a while.

399
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:02,381
I hate to interrupt the fun,

400
00:23:02,447 --> 00:23:04,850
but there's something
I wanna share with everyone today.

401
00:23:04,916 --> 00:23:05,917
Huh?

402
00:23:07,419 --> 00:23:08,954
Well, um…

403
00:23:09,588 --> 00:23:13,592
The initial reason that I came here,
or my motivation,

404
00:23:13,658 --> 00:23:16,695
was to put to an end
my 15-year relationship

405
00:23:17,195 --> 00:23:18,864
and start a new one.

406
00:23:18,930 --> 00:23:20,665
I wanted to feel excitement.

407
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:25,604
And even at 40, I wanted to be able
to express my feelings honestly.

408
00:23:25,670 --> 00:23:27,939
That's why I came here.

409
00:23:28,006 --> 00:23:31,977
But I did a lot of thinking
while living here with y'all,

410
00:23:32,043 --> 00:23:37,549
and I began to feel it would be good
to look back on the 15 years.

411
00:23:37,616 --> 00:23:40,185
Mmm. And, for example…

412
00:23:40,886 --> 00:23:43,355
Um, I made miso soup here pretty often,

413
00:23:43,422 --> 00:23:46,191
<i>and you'd all drink it</i>
<i>and tell me how good it was.</i>

414
00:23:46,691 --> 00:23:49,661
I used to make it often
when my ex and I lived together,

415
00:23:50,162 --> 00:23:53,298
and I remembered how he used
to tell me it was really good too.

416
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:56,501
When Jobu talked about
watching the movie with his ex,

417
00:23:56,568 --> 00:23:59,070
<i>I could really relate</i>
<i>to what he was saying.</i>

418
00:23:59,137 --> 00:24:02,574
I remembered how happy we were,
laughing together.

419
00:24:03,675 --> 00:24:06,344
When Taeheon talked about love,

420
00:24:06,411 --> 00:24:11,349
you said that enduring and forgiving
are also forms of love.

421
00:24:12,083 --> 00:24:13,752
<i>I could really relate to that,</i>

422
00:24:15,020 --> 00:24:16,254
and when I thought about it,

423
00:24:16,321 --> 00:24:19,891
I realized that my partner
had done that for me too.

424
00:24:20,392 --> 00:24:24,095
When I told him that I needed to be alone,

425
00:24:24,162 --> 00:24:27,499
he… he really… he hardly said anything.

426
00:24:27,566 --> 00:24:31,770
He said, "Okay, I understand.
Let's both be alone and think."

427
00:24:32,437 --> 00:24:35,574
Looking back, I've come to realize

428
00:24:36,308 --> 00:24:38,710
that he accepted all of me.

429
00:24:39,311 --> 00:24:41,046
I was able to realize that.

430
00:24:43,181 --> 00:24:44,916
So I decided…

431
00:24:46,051 --> 00:24:49,454
to continue the 15-year relationship.

432
00:24:50,322 --> 00:24:52,057
To try one more time.

433
00:24:53,592 --> 00:24:54,593
Mmm.

434
00:24:55,694 --> 00:24:58,230
That's the conclusion I came to. Yeah.

435
00:24:59,898 --> 00:25:02,701
And since I was able to come
to a solid conclusion,

436
00:25:03,702 --> 00:25:06,705
I don't get
the grand princess prize at all.

437
00:25:08,306 --> 00:25:09,574
Today, I will…

438
00:25:12,677 --> 00:25:15,180
graduate from the Green Room.

439
00:25:22,921 --> 00:25:25,557
Nice to meet you.
I'm Kazuyuki. It's good to be here.

440
00:25:25,624 --> 00:25:26,992
It's good to have you.

441
00:25:27,058 --> 00:25:29,227
I was in a relationship for 15 years.

442
00:25:30,395 --> 00:25:32,697
The thought "Am I good enough?"
just won't go away.

443
00:25:33,431 --> 00:25:36,234
A new relationship…
It'd be nice if it could happen.

444
00:25:37,102 --> 00:25:40,005
"Let's be together, then."
And that's how we got together.

445
00:25:40,071 --> 00:25:41,473
Wow, that's so nice.

446
00:25:41,973 --> 00:25:44,509
Talking about it made me
want to cry a little.

447
00:25:45,176 --> 00:25:49,381
<i>"You were crying so much next to me</i>
<i>that I started laughing halfway through."</i>

448
00:25:49,881 --> 00:25:51,883
I remembered how he used to say that.

449
00:25:53,485 --> 00:25:56,254
- Hey, wait a minute.
- Why are you crying?

450
00:25:56,321 --> 00:25:58,290
- What? Hey!
- You're so emotional.

451
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:01,860
- I was thinking how happy I am for you.
- Kazuyuki!

452
00:26:01,927 --> 00:26:04,396
After listening
to everyone's stories here,

453
00:26:04,462 --> 00:26:07,365
I'm starting to think

454
00:26:07,866 --> 00:26:11,303
that our relationship was
already in its final form.

455
00:26:11,803 --> 00:26:13,705
<i>Oh, oh, oh</i>

456
00:26:13,805 --> 00:26:18,310
<i>We used to dive</i>
<i>In our highest feelings </i>

457
00:26:18,376 --> 00:26:20,845
<i>Are we growing older together? </i>

458
00:26:20,912 --> 00:26:22,414
<i>Oh, oh, oh…</i>

459
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:25,083
I CRIED SO MUCH

460
00:26:26,251 --> 00:26:30,689
I was able to come up with
a solid answer for myself.

461
00:26:30,755 --> 00:26:33,792
I hope y'all can find
your own answers too,

462
00:26:33,858 --> 00:26:35,660
so you don't end up with regrets.

463
00:26:37,329 --> 00:26:38,997
I'm rooting for you.

464
00:26:40,365 --> 00:26:42,467
- I'm rooting for you too.
- Thanks.

